Pre-Game Insights: Oman beat Namibia by 32 runs but lost against Netherland by 4 runs in practice games.
Papua New Guinea showed good fight but lost both practice games.
Khawar Ali might open or can strengthen middle order and is a very good allrounder providing points in both departments.
Zeeshan Maqsood will handle the middle order and is a good player who will bat in the top order.
A Vala will bat 1 down, is captain of the side, and a good allrounder who can also provide points through his off break.
CJA Amini is a very good player who also bowls leg break spin.
Kaleemullah and Bilal Khan will lead the pace attack for Oman.
N Vanua, N Pokana, and D Ravu will lead the pace attack for Papua New Guinea.
Captain Choice: Z Maqsood, C Amini
Vice-Captain Choice: A Ilyas, K Ali
